Description: multifunction timer: regular timer, countdown, and stopwatch.
 ÂµTimer (or "uTimer") is a multifunction timer (command-line interface)
 which features a timer, a countdown, and a stopwatch (not available yet).
 .
 It can be very useful for "command-line geeks" or even for scripts.
 Compared to the sleep bash function, you can see the current elapsed time!
 .
 This is a relatively small program written in C using Glib, it contains
 a man page with a full description about how to use it.
 .
 See 'man utimer' or 'utimer --help' for help.
